  <h1>Trail Info CLI Gem</h1>
  <div class="projectDescription">
    <h3>TrailInfo is a CLI gem programmed to allow the user to select a state and then display available trails in that state from TrailLink.com. Users are then able to select a trail from that list to see further details about the trail.</h3>
  </div>

  <div class="projectImages">

      <%= link_to image_tag("trail_info/screenshot3.png", :alt => "trail-screenshot1", :class => "trailInfoPic project projectItemPic", :id => "trail-screenshot1"), image_path("trail_info/screenshot3.png"), :target => "blank" %>
      <%= link_to image_tag("trail_info/screenshot5.png", :alt => "trail-screenshot2", :class => "trailInfoPic project projectItemPic", :id => "trail-screenshot2"), image_path("trail_info/screenshot5.png"), :target => "blank" %>
      <%= link_to image_tag("trail_info/screenshot7.png", :alt => "trail-screenshot3", :class => "trailInfoPic project projectItemPic", :id => "trail-screenshot3"), image_path("trail_info/screenshot7.png"), :target => "blank" %>
